==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rhetorical
<hw>Rhe*tor"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rhetoricus</ets>, Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/. See <er>Rhetoric</er>.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to rhetoric; according to, or exhibiting,
rhetoric; oratorical; <as>as, the <ex>rhetorical</ex> art; a
<ex>rhetorical</ex> treatise; a <ex>rhetorical</ex>
flourish.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They permit him to leave their poetical taste ungratified,
provided that he gratifies their <qex>rhetorical</qex> sense.</q>
<rj><qau>M. Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rhe*tor"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Rhe*tor"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhetoricate</ent>⟦br⟧
